What better power source to power your car! Well, maybe not down here on Earth just yet but what about the moon or mars. Petrol stations are few and far between on other planet's although I'm certain the oil companies would build there if they could make a profit out of it.<br>
Solar power is one option ofcourse and so is extracting fuel from rocks. However, if you want a rover that can really get out of a tough spot like a steep crater or landslide then you want to go nuclear. Especially if the vehicle has to return home for refueling. Using a nuclear reactor to power your buggy means a wider area can be covered which would be vital for a rescue mission.<br>
Exploring and prospecting an entire World is going to take a very long time no matter what engines are used. Why put up with tediously slow chemical or solar powered ones and make it even harder on ourselves. Human lifetimes are limited so if faced with the option of a slow ponderous vehicle or a tough faster one that can carry more people and instruments over more terrain I think the choice is clear. <br>
